> >
> > How do other people hold in their screens on their louvered windows?
>
> Steve,
>
> On my '73, the screen frame lifts into a deep slot at the top of the
> window, then drops into a shallow slot at the bottom.  I have no plastic
> clips at all.

>                            Steve Dolan

Correct, gravity holds them in. The little plastic thingies are there to stop
the screens from rattling.
Early screens, like 68 to 71, had a little plastic tab on the top and bottom
that you would twist to hold them in tight.

